WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:31.697 --> 00:00:33.566
ERIKA LARSEN: The Sami are by
tradition reindeer herders

00:00:33.566 --> 00:00:36.035
that have lived as nomads.

00:00:36.035 --> 00:00:37.503
Everything revolved
around reindeer.

00:00:37.503 --> 00:00:43.076
The food, the children, the
stories... everything.

00:00:43.076 --> 00:00:45.478
Herders were working so
in tandem with nature

00:00:45.478 --> 00:00:48.981
that they could interpret the
Arctic to the rest of the world.

00:00:48.981 --> 00:00:51.051
The Sami people have
their own voice

00:00:51.051 --> 00:00:53.052
and their own way to tell
the world who they were.

00:00:53.052 --> 00:00:56.188
(SAMI YOIK CHANTING)

00:00:56.188 --> 00:00:59.092
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

00:01:03.196 --> 00:01:07.166 line:0%
I'm going to open tonight
with a journal entry.

00:01:07.166 --> 00:01:11.337 line:0%
November 2010, reindeer
herd separation.

00:01:11.337 --> 00:01:14.573
Dusatatsva, Norway.

00:01:14.573 --> 00:01:16.475
'I'm not ready to
leave this place,

00:01:16.475 --> 00:01:19.111
the longer I stay the
more it suits me.

00:01:19.111 --> 00:01:20.880
The land is like
a magnet,

00:01:20.880 --> 00:01:24.217
a person can either repel or
connect to this landscape.

00:01:24.217 --> 00:01:26.419
I woke up this morning
and the lavut closest

00:01:26.419 --> 00:01:28.988
to ours revealed it had
snowed all night.

00:01:28.988 --> 00:01:30.824
It was covered like a
white sugar almond

00:01:30.824 --> 00:01:33.960
that one might have received
as a wedding favor.

00:01:33.960 --> 00:01:37.831
But as this world becomes more
real to me the other fades away.

00:01:37.831 --> 00:01:40.566
I came here to find people
of when the land speaks

00:01:40.566 --> 00:01:42.936
could interpret
it's language.

00:01:42.936 --> 00:01:44.703
I came here in
search of silence

00:01:44.703 --> 00:01:47.240
so that I could begin
to hear again.

00:01:47.240 --> 00:01:50.243
I am now more a stranger in
my own home than here.'

00:01:54.146 --> 00:01:57.750
So tonight I want to take you to
the Scandinavian Arctic,

00:01:57.750 --> 00:02:00.386
where I encountered
the Sami people.

00:02:00.386 --> 00:02:02.321
The Sami are by
tradition reindeer herders

00:02:02.321 --> 00:02:04.189
that have lived
as nomads.

00:02:04.189 --> 00:02:07.727
Today they are considered the
indigenous group of Europe.

00:02:07.727 --> 00:02:10.162
To create this body of work, I
lived there for four years

00:02:10.162 --> 00:02:12.198
and worked as a beaga.

00:02:12.198 --> 00:02:14.800
A beaga is a woman
in Sami culture

00:02:14.800 --> 00:02:17.536
that would go and live with a
family of reindeer herders.

00:02:17.536 --> 00:02:21.440
She would help with the
children, she would help
cook and clean.

00:02:21.440 --> 00:02:23.442
She would also travel
with the herders

00:02:23.442 --> 00:02:24.877
when they were with
the reindeer.

00:02:24.877 --> 00:02:26.546
She would help
slaughter the reindeer,

00:02:26.546 --> 00:02:29.415
and basically anything
that needed to be done.

00:02:31.217 --> 00:02:34.487
Um, but first let's
watch a small video.

00:02:34.487 --> 00:02:38.157
This ran with my
article in 2011.

